<SiteLayout title="Mault AI Coder Guide | Setup and Governance Workflow" description="A practical guide to installing Mault, reading findings, governing AI coding actions, and reviewing evidence." canonical="/docs/ai-coder-guide/"><header class="mp-hero"><div class="shell"><p class="eyebrow">Documentation / AI Coder Guide</p><h1 class="display">From agent output to <span class="gradient-text">governed action.</span></h1><p class="lede">A practical walkthrough of the Mault development workflow.</p></div></header><section class="section"><div class="shell mp-doc-layout"><nav class="mp-doc-nav"><a href="#install">Install</a><a href="#analyze">Analyze</a><a href="#remediate">Remediate</a><a href="#enforce">Enforce</a><a href="#evidence">Evidence</a></nav><article class="mp-doc"><h2 id="install">1. Install in the coding workflow</h2><p>Connect Mault to the supported editor or coding agent used for the governed repository. Production authentication, repository access, and policy configuration are deployment-specific.</p><pre><code>mault init --repository ./project<br/>mault policy use production</code></pre><h2 id="analyze">2. Analyze project structure</h2><p>Core continuously evaluates architecture, directory health, naming, configuration, dependency flow, and structural drift.</p><ul><li>Review findings inside the Mault panel.</li><li>Inspect the affected path and rule.</li><li>Dismiss an accepted exception or prepare remediation.</li></ul><h2 id="remediate">3. Remediate with an AI coding assistant</h2><p>Use the copy-ready prompt to give the coding agent precise context. Mault keeps the finding, scope, and intended outcome connected.</p><pre><code>finding: architectural_drift<br/>target: src/services/payment.ts<br/>required_boundary: domain/ports</code></pre><h2 id="enforce">4. Enforce production policy</h2><p>Pro moves from detection to automatic enforcement. A non-compliant commit or protected action is blocked before it can ship.</p><h2 id="evidence">5. Review sealed evidence</h2><p>Each governed decision preserves identity, agent, intent, affected scope, policy, outcome, and execution evidence for engineering and security review.</p><div class="mp-panel"><h3>Next step</h3><p>See the same governance model mapped to your team’s coding tools.</p><a class="button" href="/docs/integrations/">Browse integrations</a></div></article></div></section></SiteLayout>
